cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

The paper discusses a machine reading system that leverages a rulebase of preconditions and effects of actions to answer questions about processes described in procedural text. This involves natural language processing (NLP) and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques, which are commonly associated with the computer science sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The system also uses commonsense knowledge of persistence, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.LG (Learning). Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of the system against two reading comprehension (RC) baselines, which could relate to the sub-categories of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
